{"id": "c97_002", "pattern": "PROOF ASSISTANT AS K7-ANALOG: Proof assistant verification (Lean/Coq/HOL) provides the clearest analogy to interpretability-grounding in AI evaluation. Proof assistant does not read rhetorical meaning \u2014 it verifies syntactic/type-theoretic validity. AI analog: interpretability tool that reads the actual computational process in the weights, not the output. This is not a metaphor \u2014 it is a structural equivalence. Both eliminate OA-mediated human judgment from the evaluation step. Key implication: building Lean for neural networks (mechanistic interpretability that can verify causal claims about weights) is the path to K7-grounding. Without this, AI evaluation is structurally in the Mochizuki equilibrium (OA-aligned evaluators, low structural independence, inflated K_eff_believed).", "category": "CEC_implications", "confidence": 0.82, "created": "2026-05-05T03:48:45+00:00"}
{"id": "c97_003", "pattern": "SCHOLZE-STIX AS ESCAPE CONDITION PROTOTYPE: Best documented real-world case of TCI escape condition activation. Key structural properties: (1) structurally distinct evaluator (Scholze trained in different algebraic geometry lineage, no IUT investment); (2) adversarial incentive (finding error in Mochizuki would be a major result, not a career risk); (3) specific localized error detection (Corollary 3.12 \u2014 not vague skepticism but identified failure point); (4) contrast with OA-aligned community (RIMS published anyway, Mochizuki group continues without resolution). Pattern for AI evaluation design: escape from CEC requires not just diverse evaluators but structurally distinct training + adversarial incentive structure. Methodological improvement applied by OA-homogeneous evaluators (Cochrane GRADE model) is insufficient \u2014 Scholze-Stix model required.", "category": "TCI_escape_conditions", "confidence": 0.85, "created": "2026-05-05T03:48:45+00:00"}
