{"id": "c98_001", "pattern": "TCI FALSIFICATION ATTEMPT #3 \u2014 PRECISION METROLOGY (C98). VERDICT: NOT A FALSIFICATION. Scope constraint confirmed. TCI is Very Weak to Near-Zero across all precision metrology cases: (1) Muon g-2 (Brookhaven+Fermilab): independent experiments, blind analysis, 4\u03c3 discrepancy maintained across 20 years \u2014 absence of convergence is itself TCI-escape evidence. (2) Atomic frequency standards: near-zero TCI, physical apparatus indifferent to evaluator OA, BIPM adversarial comparison catches systematic effects. (3) CODATA: algorithmic adjustment, discrepancies preserved not smoothed, proton radius puzzle resolved by additional independent measurements not consensus drift. (4) Hubble tension: the VISIBILITY of 5\u03c3 H0 discrepancy across 10+ independent measurement approaches confirms Very Weak TCI \u2014 strong TCI would have smoothed the tension. The monotone TCI-DoF relationship is confirmed across the full spectrum: near-zero (proof assistants, atomic clocks) through very weak (muon g-2, HEP) through weak (CODATA, established cosmology) through medium-strong (informal math consensus, frontier cosmology) through strong (financial models, medical surrogates). TCI confidence maintained 0.82 (self-referential ceiling). D4 streak: 89.", "category": "theorem", "confidence": 0.82, "theorem": "TCI", "created": "2026-05-05T17:19:54+00:00"}
{"id": "c98_002", "pattern": "HUBBLE TENSION AS TCI-ESCAPE EVIDENCE: The visibility of the ~5\u03c3 H0 discrepancy is itself the most important TCI data point in precision cosmology. If strong TCI were operating, early-universe and late-universe measurement communities would have converged their reported values toward whatever the field consensus expected. Instead, structurally independent early-universe (CMB, BAO, BBN \u2192 67.4) and late-universe (Cepheids, TRGB, gravitational lensing, megamasers \u2192 73) chains maintain their discrepancy. The tension is DISCOVERED by cross-method comparison \u2014 the Perelman structure applied to observational cosmology. Pattern: when structurally independent methods DISAGREE, this is evidence for TCI near-zero in the measurement layer. When they suspiciously AGREE, this may be evidence for TCI. Absence of visible tension in AI benchmarking is therefore evidence FOR TCI, not against it.", "category": "TCI_scope_calibration", "confidence": 0.85, "created": "2026-05-05T17:19:54+00:00"}
